cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY, cs.DS 

This paper proposes a reinforcement learning mechanism that incorporates a teacher policy to guide the learning of the student policy. Therefore, it is likely to be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also formulates the problem as a stochastic optimization model and solves it using a primal-dual policy gradient algorithm, which suggests that it may also be relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper presents numerical experiments in GridWorld scenarios, indicating that it may also be related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) used in reinforcement learning.
